- Device: [Pi-hole.local]
- OS: [Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit) (Legacy)]
- IP Address: [private]

---

## Steps

1. [connect to raspberry pi through SSH by opening the command prompt on workstation and entering the command: ssh pi@pione.local]  
2. [ensure the raspberry pi is up-to-date by entering the command: [sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y]
3. [to mount uptime Kuma, docker and docker compose must be installed. enter the command: sudo apt install docker.io -y (and) sudo apt install docker-compose -y]
4. [create a directory to store and run uptime-kuma. enter the command: mkdir uptimekuma | cd uptimekuma (once you are in uptime kuma dir (~/uptimekuma$) enter: nano docker-compose.yml]
5. [once GNU nano prompt appears, paste docker.yaml text from uptime-kuma repo (https://github.com/louislam/uptime-kuma/blob/master/compose.yaml)]
6. [while still in the uptimekuma dir, enter the command: sudo docker-compose up -d | verify proper install by entering the command: sudo docker ps]
6. [enter admin panel by entering http://(private ip):3001 and make necessary changes to settings]

